The paper focuses on cross-modal retrieval using visual and textual data, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) domains. The use of self-supervised learning and deep neural networks suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) as well. Finally, the use of large-scale datasets and annotations suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) as another possible sub-category.
